values: well a lot has happened since the last time i thought about writing in a journal....just a refresher....im now a freshman at uab, which so far has been one of the worst decisions of my life.  i was so stubborn when i was going through the college application process and only sent all of the necessities to one school and that was uab.  i got accepted and i thought college was going to be great.  i had a few friends already at uab, i had a steady job, and i still had my parents to fall back on.  well now that its in full swing, i see my errors in thinking.  it turns out i really dont have that many friends at uab, just a few guys from work who i occasionally talk to and then my older brother erick.  my job has gone into a downward spiral since new management came in, and i have made zero new friends at uab.  i can finally see exactly what my problem is.  i have been doing things for other people my whole life and since i quit playin sports in 11th grade, i havent done too much for myself.  this is about to come to an end.  i was eating dinner with my parents a few weeks back and i told them i wasnt liking where i was, and they told me that this is the time in my life to do what i want to do, so i brought up transferring.  at first, they were very enthusiastic about it, but lately they have taken the stand that they think im transferring for all the wrong reasons, such as going there to be with my high school friends.  for one, i could care less about most of my friends from high school.  i wouldnt care if all but like 4 or 5 fell off the face of the earth.  my reasons are that im finally ready for something new.  whats left to do in hoover?  ive been through 6 different schools since ive lived here, played 3 different sports and ive had 2 different jobs.  im ready to meet tons of new people, live in a different place for once, and finally get out on my own and do something for myself.  a long journal entry, yes, but watever, my point has finally been said exactly how i wanted
